# Committed to the repo. The token is NOT in this file -- it comes from
# the GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN env var via the ${...} interpolation below.
#
# Why this file is committed: Vercel and other CI surfaces need this
# config to resolve `@anthonycoffey/*` from GitHub Packages instead of
# npm.com. The interpolated token reference keeps secrets out of git.
#
# Local setup: set GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN in your shell with a PAT that
# has the `read:packages` scope (https://github.com/settings/tokens).
# Persistent on Windows: `setx GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN "ghp_..."` then
# open a new terminal.
#
# Vercel setup: add GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN as an env variable in the
# Vercel project (Production + Preview + Development), then redeploy.
#
# GitHub Actions: workflows in this repo authenticate via the per-run
# GITHUB_TOKEN (set in NODE_AUTH_TOKEN); see .github/workflows/*.yml.
#
# DO NOT replace the ${GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN} reference below with a
# literal token -- if you do, do not commit. Git would happily ship it.

@anthonycoffey:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_PACKAGES_TOKEN}
